FBIS4-42243 "drweu105_l_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 SPAIN Defense Minister: Troops Not in Bosnia `Forever' Defense Minister: Troops Not in Bosnia `Forever' LD3105172194 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1300 GMT 31 May 94 LD3105172194 Madrid RNE International Spanish BFN [Text] In comments for our station, Defense Minister Julian Garcia Vargas said that the blue helmets' humanitarian aid for the Bosnian conflict cannot go on forever if the parties in conflict do not reach a peace agreement. Julian Garcia Vargas. [Begin Garcia Vargas recording] We have to establish a principle: We will set a reasonable period of presence and if this period does not lead to anything, if the negotiations do not make any progress, we will have to tell the parties that we do not want to stay there forever. In two months, [corrects himself] in five months, we will have been there for two years, and I think that it is time to speak to our European partners and to discuss with them the fact that this cannot go on forever. [end recording]
